          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and chill the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the butter and sugar until pale and creamy. Beat in the egg and vanilla. Stir in the flour and salt until a smooth dough forms. Divide into two discs, wrap, and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll, cut, and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C conventional (160°C fan). Roll the chilled dough to 4 mm thick and cut into shapes. Place on lined trays with space between each. Bake for 10 to 14 minutes until barely golden at the edges. Cool completely on a rack before icing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the icing and decorate",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the egg whites with the lemon juice and cream of tartar until frothy. Add the sifted icing sugar and beat for 3 to 5 minutes until thick, smooth, and holds stiff peaks. This is the outline icing. Transfer about two-thirds to a piping bag. Thin the remainder with water, a teaspoon at a time, until it passes the 10-second flood test. Pipe outlines around the biscuits, let dry for 20 minutes, then flood inside the outlines. Leave flat for at least 1 hour until fully set.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
